org.typemeta.funcj.control

Interface Trampoline<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the value type yielded by the Trampoline
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Trampoline.FlatMapped, Trampoline.Pure, Trampoline.Suspend

    public interface Trampoline<T>
    Trampoline monad.

    The trampoline monad provides a mechanism for converting recursive computations, that may blow the stack (i.e. cause an StackOverflowError), into their iterative equivalent.

    Based on the Stackless Scala With Free Monads paper by Runar Bjarnason.

    • Nested Class Summary

      static class  Trampoline.FlatMapped<S,T>

      static class  Trampoline.Pure<T>
      Represents the end of a computation, in the form of the resultant value.
      static class  Trampoline.Suspend<T>
      Represents a continuation, indicating that further steps are required in the computation.
